progenitor of the Kreutz system.  The bullets indicate the sungrazers that
are assumed to move in the same orbit as their immediate parent.  The
sungrazers in the heavily framed boxes reached their first perihelion in
AD~363 as a swarm of daylight comets (Section~4.4).  Their orbits are
approximated as follows:\ Fragment~I by C/1843~D1; Fragment~II by C/1882~R1;
Fragment~Pe by C/1963~R1; Fragment~IIa by C/1970~K1; and Fragment~III by
C/2011~W3.  The orbits for Fragments~Ia, Pre-I, IIa$^\ast\!$ (see Section~5),
IIIa, and IV are described elsewhere in this paper. (Reproduced from
Paper~3.){\vspace{0.9cm}}}
